    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
            
            $('.tab', '#section6').click(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $(this).addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).data('id') + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($(this).index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.tab-select', '#section6').change(function() {
                $('.tab, .tab-content', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-content[data-id=' + $(this).val() + ']', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div', '#section6').removeClass('current');
                $('.tab-select .select-container div:nth-child(' +  ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').addClass('current');
                $('.select .select-container div', '#section6').show();
                $('.select .select-container div:nth-child(' + ($('.tab.current', '#section6').index() + 1) + ')', '#section6').hide();
                chkContentHeight();
            });

            $('.record-slider', '#section6').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: true
            });

            function chkContentHeight() {
                $('p.description', '#section6').each(function() {
                    if($(this).height() > 160) {
                        $(this).parent().addClass('more');
                    }
                });
            }
            chkContentHeight();

            $('.record-item article button.view-more', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-less').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').show();
            });
            $('.record-item article button.view-less', '#section6').click(function() {
                $(this).hide();
                $(this).parent().find('.view-more').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.description').show();
                $(this).parent().find('.content').hide();
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at STC?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="364">
                        <time>26/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>We recently had the incredible opportunity to invite Dr. Marvin Chung from HKU for a Cast-Making Workshop!👨‍⚕<br><br>This was a "first-time" experience for most of the participants, and it was just as challenging as it was fun! The hands-on experience gave participants a glimpse into real orthopedic medical practice, aiming to guide those interested in a future medical career, whilst fostering laughter amongst themselves - especially seeing everyone walk away with their own casts. 🦾<br><br>A huge thank you to Dr. Marvin for inspiring our future medical professionals.✨</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/369a9146ce0f6189b984a9f4e8747738.jpg" alt="657144143_1404524175021002_4514909901035018431_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="363">
                        <time>26/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>𝗢𝘂𝘁𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗕𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗶𝘀𝗵 𝗣𝗵𝘆𝘀𝗶𝗰𝘀 𝗢𝗹𝘆𝗺𝗽𝗶𝗮𝗱 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗲𝘁𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀<br><br>Our students recently participated in the Intermediate Physics Challenge (IPC) and Senior Physics Challenge (SPC) organised by the British Physics Olympiad. These rigorous competitions test fundamental physics principles and real-world applications, aiming to enhance students' lateral thinking skills and help them reach their full potential in physics.⚛<br><br>We are proud to announce that our students achieved the following awards:<br><br>🏅Gold Awards: Katherine Wen and Aaron Wang<br>🏅Silver Awards: Hayden Leung <br>🏅Bronze Awards: Isaiah Liu, Adam Pan, Jovan Wong, Purple Lau, Erin Cho, Iris Shi, and Ted Lo<br>Congratulations to all participants for their exceptional achievements and dedication!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/7ceb3d254d08fa0c546b65a4dfcf1857.jpg" alt="655689537_1404389971701089_1688721808163289155_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="362">
                        <time>25/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our students recently represented STC at the CDNIS SDG Summit, centered on the theme: “Accelerate Your Action.” ✨<br><br>From the participants to the Impact Fair to the Organising Committee (shoutout to Cathy Yang, Isaiah Liu, Nikki Moy, and Zihan Liu), our community’s presence was felt throughout. <br><br>We are also incredibly proud of our student filmmakers🎬👏. Two projects exploring food insecurity (by Angela Mak, Hazel Lam, Themis Ho, Tiffany Zhong, and Grace Chung, Kari Wan, Rosanne Wong, Tabitha Tay) were shortlisted for the Docathon showcase, while a third documentary by Gabrielle Lee, Scarlett Man, and Teresa Rana provided a powerful lens on domestic labour during the summit’s workshops.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4fadacdc8f1330d1d6e861597d5ef010.jpg" alt="658373204_1403511671788919_7511151309511047281_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="361">
                        <time>24/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Sha Tin College had a spooky week with their production of The Addams Family👪.<br><br>The strong cast and crew of 40 have been working hard all year on the dark comic musical based on the much loved characters from the US TV show📺. The show deals with what it is like to be different in a world where this is frowned upon - although to the Addams it's everyone else who seem a little peculiar! The focus of this much loved Broadway hit, focusses on the mismatched alliance of Wednesday Addams and her new love - Lucas, who struggles to be accepted. <br><br>Well done to everyone involved for entertaining us - and embracing the ethos of the quirky crew that are the Addams! 🔥🔥🔥</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/0b3f5f785749cf49f348a8fce0fc47af.jpg" alt="656291880_1402729268533826_3990527078838707402_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="360">
                        <time>23/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Eight year 11 students competed in the City University of Hong Kong  Science Patent Challenge, and on Saturday 13 March, they made their final pitch and prototype demonstration in front of the judges. 👏<br><br>Congratulations on winning 1st place🏆! The students will now have a patent attorney register their invention of a smart helmet for firefighter safety. <br><br>✨Well done to Janey XING, Jolly WONG, Jodi LEUNG, Nicholas LEE, Suan LEE, Feifan ZHANG, Purple LAU, Andy PAN.👏👏👏</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/87a7ada89cc74d53f9ea3007ca599db9.jpg" alt="654976006_1401748371965249_3036649769058985449_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="359">
                        <time>23/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>On Thursday, 19 March, STC HE team hosted a Higher Education Q&A session for Year 12 parents and guardians, following the success of our recent HE Virtual Evening.🧑‍🏫<br><br>The morning session provided a valuable opportunity for attendees to ask follow-up questions about university applications in a more intimate setting. Participants came prepared after reviewing our comprehensive FAQs, with many submitting specific queries in advance to ensure detailed responses.🗣<br><br>We were delighted to welcome a representative from a Hong Kong university, who shared expert guidance on the HK application landscape—an increasingly popular pathway for our students. The insights into admissions processes complemented the broader application advice discussed.<br><br>The session reinforced our commitment to supporting families as they navigate the early stages of higher education research, ensuring everyone leaves with clearer next steps for the journey ahead.🛣</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/584d603a861662fdf349d042ad6add5a.jpg" alt="654807975_1401709235302496_487214562623967288_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="358">
                        <time>21/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Kids’ Lit Quiz Champions!🏆<br><br>What a day of book‑loving brilliance!<br>🔹23 teams from Hong Kong and Macau battled it out in the morning heats.<br>🔹The top 6 teams faced off in a nail‑biting afternoon final.<br>🔹Our school entered 4 teams - and two made it all the way to the national<br>finals!<br><br>1st place: Lucas Hin (Y8); Lizzie Chiu (Y8); Jake Kim (Y7); and Ryan Zhou (Y7)<br>3rd place: William Chan, 8G1; Kairvi Kataria, 8D1; Christine Shi, 8P1; and Jayden Ng,<br>7D2.<br><br>Participating teams:<br>Abigail Tse (Y8); Celina Xue (Y8); Alva Lam (Y8); and Sophie Yip (Y7).<br>Veronica Lau (Y8); Jake Lam (Y8); Emma Yip (Y7); and Tyler Ding (Y7).<br><br>Now, our winning team is invited to New Zealand 🇳🇿 in July to represent Hong Kong<br>SAR at the World Championship, competing against the best from around the<br>world.<br>A huge shout‑out to all our winners and participants - you’ve made us so proud🔥!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/9af3b358fd41a5c86c44b3ea4a77d427.jpg" alt="654944185_1398990322241054_4831206154142097621_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="357">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>From 3D printing waste to New Design Frontiers🌟<br><br>Our Year 12 Design students are closing the loop on 3D printing waste! By shredding PLA waste into small chips and leveraging its thermo-softening properties, we are transforming "single-use" plastic into high-quality 3mm recycled sheets. <br><br>This inquiry unit blends material science with hands-on processing, challenging students to treat recycled plastic with the same technical rigor as industrial composites. With our new material we have called SHRED X, ready, we are moving into a material-led innovation project asking:  "What are the design opportunities that this newly developed material presents us with now?"💫</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/7a3012fed5bbd17dab7958c1a8c3aa37.jpg" alt="654648654_1398960365577383_6709993888437049145_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="356">
                        <time>19/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Big congratulations to our chess teams!🥳🥳<br><br>🎖U12 Section: Our Year 7 students took 2nd place!<br>🎖U18 Section: Year 8 and 9 students took 1st place!<br><br>Special mention to Lucas Leung (Y8) for placing 6th, Austin Tsui (Y9) 7th, Charles Tan (Y9) 8th, and Alwyn Liu (Y9) 15th in the U18 section.<br><br>Together with SJS, we proudly brought home the Dr. R. Lister Cup🏆, awarded based on results across all sections. <br><br>Well done to everyone who competed - your hard work and teamwork made us proud!💪</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/a349ff8a11e431a23157097d47329dfc.jpg" alt="653908623_1398181782321908_2427711344166466141_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="355">
                        <time>18/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>𝗜𝗕𝗗𝗣 𝗩𝗶𝘀𝘂𝗮𝗹 𝗔𝗿𝘁 𝗦𝗟/𝗛𝗟 𝗔𝗿𝘁 𝗘𝘅𝗵𝗶𝗯𝗶𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻🎨<br><br>The IBDP Visual Art SL/HL Art Exhibition showcases a year and a half of dedicated effort by our talented students✨. This ambitious event features a variety of techniques and materials, highlighting each student's unique line of inquiry.🖌<br><br>Each exhibition space reflects remarkable independence, with students exploring their themes deeply. Accounting for 40% of their final grade, this exhibition not only showcases creativity but also celebrates their hard work.<br><br>Last Tuesday’s opening was a fantastic opportunity to honor their achievements and appreciate the vibrant range of artistic expressions on display.🎖</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8fb11e81e3af339c5c16e15bc4b5edcb.jpg" alt="655237598_1397515629055190_3918284864960919126_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
