            <div class="lightbox" data-id="357">
            <div class="lightbox-wrapper">
                <button class="close"></button>
                <div class="lightbox-container">
                    <time>20/03/2026</time>
                    <div class="lightbox-content">
                                                    <h3>From 3D printing waste to New Design Frontiers🌟<br><br>Our Year 12 Design students are closing the loop on 3D printing waste! By shredding PLA waste into small chips and leveraging its thermo-softening properties, we are transforming "single-use" plastic into high-quality 3mm recycled sheets. <br><br>This inquiry unit blends material science with hands-on processing, challenging students to treat recycled plastic with the same technical rigor as industrial composites. With our new material we have called SHRED X, ready, we are moving into a material-led innovation project asking:  "What are the design opportunities that this newly developed material presents us with now?"💫</h3>
